---
title: Sweet Chili Chicken Rice Bowls with Chicken Thighs, Sesame Slaw & Quick Pickled Cucumber
description: Forget take-out: The path to sweet-hot dinner bliss is only 30 minutes away! You’ll marinate and lightly batter juicy, flavorful chicken thighs morsels, pan-fry to golden perfection, then toss with sweet Thai chili sauce. The chicken is nestled atop a bowl of fluffy rice alongside a creamy cabbage slaw with sweet pears and tangy ponzu sauce, plus crisp and tangy pickled cucumber. Garnish your bowls with crackly sesame seeds for a symphony of flavors and textures.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/655b9a8ed1348f59373b1e7e-75c767e1.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/655b9a8ed1348f59373b1e7e.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-chicken-rice-bowls-655b9a8ed1348f59373b1e7e
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: East Asia
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
