  sodium: 2580 mg
---

Pat @diced chicken thighs{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. In a #medium bowl{},
combine chicken and @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}; set aside to marinate.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} into rounds. Halve, core, and slice
@pear{1} lengthwise into ¼-inch-thick planks. Cut planks lengthwise to create
¼-inch-thick matchsticks.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for
4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat
to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

== Quick Pickled Cucumber ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{1%teaspoon},
and @salt{1%tsp} (2 tsp sugar and 2 tsp salt for 4 servings); stir until dissolved.
Add cucumber and just enough water to cover (we used ¼ cup; 1⁄3 cup for 4); stir to
coat. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Sesame Slaw ==

In a second medium bowl (large bowl for 4 servings), combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}
and @ponzu sauce{6%ml}.

Add pear, @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, and half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}; toss to
combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in splashes of cucumber pickling
liquid to taste.

== Sweet Chili Chicken ==

To bowl with marinated chicken, add @cornstarch{2%tablespoon} and mix until chicken
is coated.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat.

Once oil is hot, add coated chicken in a single layer. Cook, undisturbed, until
browned and crispy on one side, ~{2-3%minutes}. Flip chicken (the pieces will
stick together, so you can turn the chicken easily). Cook, separating chicken
into pieces, until cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Wash and dry bowl used for chicken. When chicken is done, transfer to clean
bowl. Add @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} and toss to coat.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and divide between shallow #bowls{}.

Top rice with sweet chili chicken, slaw, and pickled cucumber (draining first) in
separate sections. Sprinkle everything with remaining sesame seeds and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.